      • compileFunction

        static CallableUserFunction compileFunction​(UserFunctionSignature signature,
                                            List<FieldSetter> fieldSetters,
                                            Method methodToCall)
                                     throws ProcedureException
        Generates code for a user-defined function.

        Given a user-defined function defined by 

             class MyClass {
       @Context
        public Log log;

       @UserFunction
        public double addPi(long value) {
            return value + Math.PI;
        }
     }

        we will generate something like 

             class GeneratedAddPi implements CallableUserFunction {
         public static UserFunctionSignature SIGNATURE;
         public static FieldSetter SETTER_0;

         public AnyValue apply(Context ctx, AnyValue[] input) {
              try {
                  MyClass userClass = new MyClass();
                  userClass.log = (Log) SETTER_0.get(ctx);
                  return Values.doubleValue(userClass.addPi( ((NumberValue) input[0]).longValue() );
              } catch (Throwable T) {
                  throw new ProcedureException([appropriate error msg], T);
              }
         }

         public UserFunctionSignature signature() {return SIGNATURE;}
     }

        where the static fields are set once during loading via reflection.

        Parameters:
        signature - the signature of the user-defined function
        fieldSetters - the fields to set before each call.
        methodToCall - the method to call
        Returns:
        a CallableUserFunction delegating to the underlying user-defined function.
        Throws:
        ProcedureException - if something went wrong when compiling the user-defined function.

      • compileProcedure

        static CallableProcedure compileProcedure​(ProcedureSignature signature,
                                          List<FieldSetter> fieldSetters,
                                          Method methodToCall)
                                   throws ProcedureException
        Generates code for a user-defined procedure.

        Given a user-defined function defined by 

             class MyClass {
       @Context
        public Log log;

       @Procedure
        public Stream myStream(long value) {
            ...
        }
     }

        we will generate something like 

             class GeneratedMyStream implements CallableProcedure {
         public static ProcedureSignature SIGNATURE;
         public static FieldSetter SETTER_0;

          RawIterator apply( Context ctx, AnyValue[] in, ResourceTracker tracker ) throws ProcedureException {
              try {
                  MyClass userClass = new MyClass();
                  userClass.log = (Log) SETTER_0.get(ctx);
                  Stream fromUser = userClass.myStream(((NumberValue) input[0]).longValue() );
                  return new GeneratedIterator(fromUser, tracker, SIGNATURE);
              } catch (Throwable T) {
                  throw new ProcedureException([appropriate error msg], T);
              }
         }

         public ProcedureSignature signature() {return SIGNATURE;}
     }

        where the static fields are set once during loading via reflection and where the GeneratedIterator implements the appropriate mapping from user-types Object[] to AnyValue[].

        Parameters:
        signature - the signature of the procedure
        fieldSetters - the fields to set before each call.
        methodToCall - the method to call
        Returns:
        a CallableProcedure delegating to the underlying procedure method.
        Throws:
        ProcedureException - if something went wrong when compiling the user-defined function.

      • compileAggregation

        static CallableUserAggregationFunction compileAggregation​(UserFunctionSignature signature,
                                                          List<FieldSetter> fieldSetters,
                                                          Method create,
                                                          Method update,
                                                          Method result)
                                                   throws ProcedureException
        Generates code for a user-defined aggregation function.

        Given a user-defined aggregation function defined by 

             class MyClass {
       @Context
        public Log log;

       @UserAggregationFunction
        public Adder create() {
            return new Adder;
        }
     }

     class Adder {
       private long sum;
       @UserAggregationUpdate
       public void update(long in) {
           sum += in;
       }
       @UserAggregationResult
       public long result() {
         return sum;
       }
    }
     }

        we will generate two classe looking something like 

             class Generated implements CallableUserAggregationFunction {
         public static UserFunctionSignature SIGNATURE;
         public static FieldSetter SETTER_0;

         public UserAggregator create(Context ctx) {
              try {
                  MyClass userClass = new MyClass();
                  userClass.log = (Log) SETTER_0.get(ctx);
                  return new GeneratedAdder(userClass.create());
              } catch (Throwable T) {
                  throw new ProcedureException([appropriate error msg], T);
              }
         }

         public UserFunctionSignature signature() {return SIGNATURE;}
     }
     class GeneratedAdder implements UserAggregator {
       private Adder adder;

       GeneratedAdder(Adder adder) {
         this.adder = adder;
       }

       void update(AnyValue[] in) {
          adder.update(((NumberValue) in).longValue());
       }

       AnyValue result() {
          return adder.result(Values.longValue(adder.result());
       }
     }

        where the static fields are set once during loading via reflection.

        Parameters:
        signature - the signature of the user-defined function
        fieldSetters - the fields to set before each call.
        create - the method that creates the aggregator
        update - the update method of the aggregator
        result - the result method of the aggregator
        Returns:
        a CallableUserFunction delegating to the underlying user-defined function.
        Throws:
        ProcedureException - if something went wrong when compiling the user-defined function.

        outputType - the output type of the user procedure

        userClass.field1 = (type1) SETTER_1.get(context) userClass.field2 = (type2) SETTER_2.get(context) ... return [CONVERT TO AnyVALUE](userClass.call( [CONVERT_TO_JAVA] input[0], ... );

      • unboxIfNecessary

        private static Expression unboxIfNecessary​(Class<?> fieldType,
                                           Expression invoke)
        Used for properly setting a primitive field For example say that the class has a field of type long. Then we will generate the RHS of. 
             userClass.longField = ((Long) invoke).longValue()
        Parameters:
        fieldType - the type of the field
        invoke - the expression used to set the field
        Returns:
        an expression where casting and boxing/unboxing has been taken care of.

      • fromAnyValue

        private static Expression fromAnyValue​(Class<?> expectedType,
                                       Expression expression,
                                       CodeBlock block,
                                       Expression context)
        Converts from an `AnyValue` to the type specified by the procedure or function.

        In a lot of cases we can figure out the conversion statically, for example `LongValue` will be turned into ((LongValue) value).longValue() etc. For composite types as Lists and Maps and also for Graph types such as Nodes, Relationships and Paths we will use a ValueMapper.

        Parameters:
        expectedType - the java type expected by the procedure or function
        expression - an expression that will evaluate to an AnyValue
        block - The current code block.
        context - The current context.
        Returns:
        an expression properly typed to be consumed by function or procedure
